class.name: IDMCircle2D
class.abstract: OLE for Design and Modeling 2D Circle Definition.

method.name: GetCircleData
method.abstract: Returns the circle's parameters.

class.name: IDMCurve2D
class.abstract: OLE for Design and Modeling 2D Curve Definition.

method.name: GetContinuity
method.abstract: This method returns the highest level of geometric continuity, the curve possesses.

method.name: GetCurvature
method.abstract: Given an array of parameters on the curve, this method computes the curvature of the curve at that point.

method.name: GetCurveType
method.abstract: There is a specific type associated with the curve geometry.

method.name: GetDerivatives
method.abstract: Given an array of parameters on the curve, this method evaluates the derivatives of the curve at these points.

method.name: GetEndPoints
method.abstract: This method returns the end-points of the curve.

method.name: GetGeometryForm
method.abstract: This method returns high-level geometric property information that characterizes this curve-based object.

method.name: GetLengthAtParam
method.abstract: This method outputs the length, measured along the curve, from a given parameter to a given parameter.

method.name: GetParamAnomaly
method.abstract: Typically, a curve's parametric space can be expected to be finite.

method.name: GetParamAtLength
method.abstract: This method outputs the parameter at a given length, measured along the curve, starting from a given parameter.

method.name: GetParamAtPoint
method.abstract: Given an array of 2D points lying near the curve, in the local coordinate system (X, Y) of the curve, this method computes the parameter on the curve that corresponds to them.

method.name: GetParamExtents
method.abstract: This method returns the parametric extents of the curve.

method.name: GetPointAtParam
method.abstract: Given an array of parameters on the curve, this method computes the corresponding 2D space points (X, Y) in the curve's local coordinate system.

method.name: GetRangeBox
method.abstract: The range box (also known as bounding box) is axially-aligned within the local coordinate system of the Server.

method.name: GetTangent
method.abstract: Given an array of parameter values on the curve, this method computes the unit-vector tangent at each of the points.

class.name: IDMPoint2D
class.abstract: OLE for Design and Modeling 2D Point Definition.

method.name: GetPointData
method.abstract: Returns the information that fully describe the point.

class.name: IDMPolyline2D
class.abstract: OLE for Design and Modeling 2D Polyline Definition.

method.name: GetPolylineData
method.abstract: Obtains the points that fully define the polyline.

method.name: GetPolylineInfo
method.abstract: Returns overall information related to the polyline.
